Veel van de opties die invloed hebben op het spel kunnen in OpenTTD worden veranderd. Veel van deze opties kunnen via het [[nl/Archive/Manual/Settings/Geavanceerde instellingen|geavanceerde instellingen]]-venster gewijzigd worden, maar voor sommige moet je het configuratiebestand [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Openttd.cfg|openttd.cfg (EN)]] bewerken. Meest geavanceerde instellingen verbeteren het spel of de interface, terwijl andere je meer mogelijkheden geven in het spel.

==Geavanceerde instellingen wijzigen==
[[File:en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Advanced options full.png|thumb|left|De volledig uitgeklapte geavanceerde instellingen boom]]
{{en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Advanced Settings}}
Het '''Geavanceerde instellingen''' venster laat je de meeste beschikbare geavanceerde instellingen in het spel aanpassen. Het heeft een boom-structuur, onderverdeeld in de volgende hoofd-secties:

*[[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Advanced Settings/Interface|Interface]]
*[[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Advanced Settings/Construction|Construction]]
*[[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Advanced Settings/Vehicles|Vehicles]]
*[[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Advanced Settings/Stations|Stations]]
*[[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Advanced Settings/Economy|Economy]]
*[[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Advanced Settings/Competitors|Competitors]]

Buttons are green to show the setting is on, red to show it is off. Arrow buttons change the value of the setting like a horizontal scrollbox. Clicking on a patch-line with arrow buttons shown will bring up an edit box, where the desired value can be typed in.

Some features that have been advanced settings (patches) in older versions of OpenTTD can now be found under [[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Difficulty|difficulty settings]], [[en/Manual/Game options window|game options]] or [[en/Manual/Cheats]]. Some of them might even have become permanent features that you cannot disable.{{en/-}}

==Trivia==
The Advanced Settings windows was previously (prior to OpenTTD 0.7.x) known as the ''[[en/Archive/Manual/Settings/Configuring patches|Configure Patches]] window''. This name came from [[en/Archive/OpenTTD/TTDPatch]] and was used in OpenTTD as well for quite some time.

Since r14275, the name ''Patches'' was dropped in favour of "Advanced Settings" in order to avoid confusion with TTDPatch in general, or patches (in the technical sense) against the source code of OpenTTD often found in the [http://www.tt-forums.net/viewforum.php?f=33 Development section of tt-forums].

Since r14974 the tabs at the top of the window are removed and all advanced settings are listed in a tree structure. This allows for subcategories that can be expanded and collapsed independently. The former tabs (''Interface'', ''Construction'', ''Vehicles'', ''Stations'', ''Economy'' and ''Competitors'') are now top level categories and they can now have subcategories, for example the subcategory ''Trains'' in ''Vehicles''.


